  "prompt": "What is the meaning of tax rebate? As per the year budget, tax rebate is now 5000 for salary more than 5 lakh. What does it mean in a lay man language?",
  "response": "Let me explain tax rebate in simple terms:\n\nA tax rebate is a reduction in the amount of income tax you need to pay. It's like a discount on your tax bill.\n\nIn the recent budget, for someone earning up to \u20b97.5 lakhs per year:\n- If your total income is \u20b95-7.5 lakhs, you can get a rebate of \u20b95,000\n- This means you won't have to pay any tax on that amount\n\nExample:\n1. Let's say your annual salary is \u20b96 lakhs\n2. Normally, you would pay tax on the amount above \u20b95 lakhs\n3. But with this rebate, you get \u20b95,000 off your tax liability\n4. So effectively, you pay zero tax\n\nKey points:\n- It reduces your tax burden\n- Applies to those in lower income brackets\n- Helps provide some financial relief to middle-income earners\n- Encourages tax compliance\n\nIn simple words, it means the government is giving you a little financial break by reducing the tax you need to pay.",
